init_text: When you die, you appear in a cinema with a number of other people who look like you. You find out that they are your previous reincarnations, and soon you all begin watching your next life on the big screen.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You can control the movie by making a series of choices.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The film shows you as a child, growing up.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: When you're about twenty, the movie jumps forward to show your thirties.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You can see yourself making the same mistakes over and over again.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You are trapped in a vicious cycle, and you can't seem to break out.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You love what you are now doing for a living, and for the first time in your life, you feel satisfied with your lot.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: A new house, a new car, vacations.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You tell yourself that it's okay because you have the money now to help people who need it.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You give money to a few different organizations, vowing to personally help the people they cater to.
